  "prompt": "What are the best hotels to stay at in San Francisco?",
  "response": "San Francisco offers a wide range of hotels catering to various preferences and budgets. Here are some of the best options across different categories:\n\n### Luxury Hotels\n1. **Fairmont San Francisco** - A historic hotel with stunning views, luxurious amenities, and a prime location near Nob Hill.\n2. **The Ritz-Carlton, San Francisco** - Known for its elegance and exceptional service, it offers a luxurious experience with spacious rooms and fine dining.\n3. **Hotel Nikko San Francisco** - Features modern amenities, a Japanese-inspired aesthetic, and is conveniently located near Union Square.\n\n### Boutique Hotels\n1. **Mystic Hotel by Charlie Palmer** - A stylish hotel with a vibrant atmosphere, located near Union Square.\n2. **Hotel Zephyr** - A fun, waterfront boutique hotel with eclectic decor and easy access to Pier 39 and Fisherman\u2019s Wharf.\n3. **Hotel G** - An artful boutique hotel in the heart of Union Square, blending modern design and comfort.\n\n### Budget-Friendly Options\n1. **HI San Francisco Downtown Hostel** - A friendly hostel offering dormitory and private rooms, situated in a central location with various amenities.\n2. **Green Tortoise Hostel** - Known for its lively atmosphere and social vibe, this hostel is located near Fisherman\u2019s Wharf.\n3. **Travelodge by Wyndham Presidio San Francisco** - An affordable option with comfortable accommodations near the Presidio and Golden Gate Park.\n\n### Mid-Range Hotels\n1. **The Kimpton Alton Hotel** - A stylish hotel with a great location near Fisherman\u2019s Wharf and Ghirardelli Square.\n2. **Hotel Rex** - A charming hotel with a literary theme and a cozy ambiance, located close to Union Square.\n3. **The Marina Inn** - A budget-friendly choice with comfortable rooms and a great location near the Marina District.\n\n### Unique Stays\n1. **Cova Hotel** - Offers a welcoming atmosphere with a rooftop terrace and easy access to Civic Center and Union Square.\n2. **Argonaut Hotel** - A unique waterfront hotel with a nautical theme, situated in a former cannery next to Fisherman\u2019s Wharf.\n3. **The Clift Royal Sonesta Hotel** - A blend of modern luxury and historic charm, known for its stunning lobby and vibrant bar.\n\nWhen choosing a hotel, consider your preferred location, amenities, and budget. San Francisco's public transportation system makes it easy to get around, so you can choose accommodations in various neighborhoods while still accessing popular attractions.",
